Model: Observations

\(I_t\) is an index of biomass \(B_t\).

\[I_t = q B_t.\]

Model on the depletion scale, \(P_t = B_t / K\).

\[I_t \sim \operatorname{\log\ Normal}\left( \log(q K P_t), \tau^2 \right)\]

  • I_t is then log-normally distributed
  • Will come back to this; can be represented multiple ways

Model: Population dynamics

\[\begin{aligned} P_1 \mid \sigma^2 &\sim \operatorname{log\ Normal}(0, \sigma^2)\\ \tilde{P}_t &= P_{t-1} + r P_{t-1}(1 - P_{t-1}) - \frac{C_{t-1}}{K}\\ P_{t} \mid P_{t-1},K,r,\sigma^2 &\sim \operatorname{log\ Normal}\left(\log(\tilde{P}_{t-1}), \sigma^2\right)\\ \end{aligned}\]

  • Schaefer dynamics
  • Intrinsic growth rate \(r\)
  • log-Normal error with sd \(\sigma\)
  • \(P_1\) near \(1\)

Model: Prior

All but \(q\) at least somewhat informative, based on literature review. Specified \(\log(q) \sim \operatorname{Flat}\).

\[\begin{aligned} r &\sim \operatorname{log Normal}(-1.38, 0.51^2)\\ K &\sim \operatorname{log Normal}(5.04, 0.5162^2)\\ p(q) &\propto 1/q\\ \sigma^2 &\sim \operatorname{Inverse Gamma}(3.79, 0.0102)\\ \tau^2 &\sim \operatorname{Inverse Gamma}(1.71, 0.0086). \end{aligned}\]

Noncentered Normal process errors

\[\begin{aligned} P_1 \mid \sigma^2 &= \exp(u_1 \sigma)\\ P_t \mid P_{t-1},\dots &= \bigg[ P_{t-1} + r P_{t-1}(1 - P_{t-1}) \\ & \quad \quad \quad \quad - \frac{C_{t-1}}{K} \bigg] \exp(u_t \sigma)\\ u_t &\sim \operatorname{Normal}(0, 1) \end{aligned}\]

Constrained P

\[P_{t-1} + r P_{t-1} (1 - P_{t-1}) - \frac{C_{t-1}}{K} > 0\]

\[P_{t-1} \in \left( \frac{1 + r \mp \sqrt{(1 + r)^2 - 4 r C_t / K}}{2r}\right)\]

Explicit F parameterization

\[\begin{aligned} C^*_t = &\exp(-F_t) K \left[P_t + r P_t (1 - P_t)\right]\\ C_t \sim &\operatorname{Normal}(C^*_t, \xi^2)\\ P_1 \mid \sigma^2 \sim &\operatorname{log\ Normal}(1, \sigma^2)\\ \tilde{P}_t \mid P_{t-1},\dots = &\left[ P_{t-1} + r P_{t-1}(1 - P_{t-1})\right]\\ &\times (1 - \exp(-F_{t-1}))\\ P_t \sim &\operatorname{log Normal}(\tilde{P}_{t-1}, \sigma^2) \quad t=2,\dots,T \end{aligned}\]

  • ERROR HERE - Not what I coded; catches don’t quite match
  • Additive error on observed catch
  • \(xi\) is fixed; don’t have any information on it
  • Test sensitivity later
  • Catch occurs after production

Marginalized \(q\)

\[\begin{aligned} Z_i &= \log\left( \frac{I_i}{P_i K} \right)\\ \hat{q}' &= \frac{1}{n} \sum_i Z_i\\ Z_i &\sim \operatorname{Normal}(\hat{q}', \tau^2) \end{aligned}\]

From Walters & Ludwig (1994), Calculation of Bayes posterior probability distributions for key populations parameters.

  • \(\hat{q}'\) is MLE of \(\log q\)
  • Prior on \(q\) also eliminated
